cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SE, cs.CV 

This paper is primarily focused on training robust tree ensembles for security applications, specifically for detecting malware, phishing, scam, and social engineering. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also proposes a new algorithm for training robust tree ensembles, which involves designing a general algorithm based on greedy heuristic, and implementing it for gradient boosted decision trees in xgboost and random forests in scikit-learn. This suggests that the paper could also belong to the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.SE (Software Engineering). Finally, the paper uses a case study to analyze attacker's cost increase to evade the robust model, which involves analyzing features and manipulating costs. This suggests that the paper could also belong to the category of cs.CV (Computer Vision).
